description:
Perform reception duties including handling incoming calls, client greeting, courier receiving, letter dispatching, mailing;
Provide office administrative supports including pantry & sundries management, water machine and vending machine maintenance, stationeries, office supplies management,  and material printing, office equipment and facilities’ maintenance, office housekeeping;
Ensure reception area and meeting rooms are tidy, presentable and well-organized;
Provide support to HR & Admin department;
Provide support to employees, company events and activities and assist in ad hoc projects as required
Requirement: 

Form 5 standard or above with 1-2 years in receptionist/administrative experience
Pleasant with good telephone manner and strong communication skills
Good command of spoken English, Chinese & Mandarin
Proficient in PC applications including MS Outlook, Word, Excel and Chinese Word Processing

Job Responsibilities

Ensure all purchases are in line with the Hotel policy;
Obtains competitive quotations and bids and ensure proper documentation for purchasing records;
Posts orders to inventory module and produce purchase order for receiver to match against goods received;
Maintain all F&B suppliers to fulfill the Hotel hygiene standard.

Job Requirements

Certificate in hotel or catering management or related field;
4-5 years related experience in the hotel industry;
Proficient in PC application and MC system;
Good communication and interpersonal skills;
Good command of English and Chinese.
